de.feig
Interface FedmIscFunctionUnitID

public interface FedmIscFunctionUnitID

Interface, containing access constants for communication parameters for the OBID i-scan® Function Units.

Copyright © 2005-2006 FEIG ELECTRONIC GmbH, All Rights Reserved.
Lange Strasse 4
D-35781 Weilburg
Federal Republic of Germany
phone : +49 6471 31090
fax : +49 6471 310999
e-mail : obid-support@feig.de
Internet : http://www.feig.de

This interface contains the access constants for communication parameters for the OBID i-scan® Function Units ID ISC.ANT.MUX and ID ISC.DAT.
The access constants play a central role in the data traffic between the application program and data containers in the class library, as well as within the class library between protocol method and data containers. They both identify the parameter and contain the storage location (in coded form) in one of the data containers. An access constant is a string and generally is structured as follows:
These access constants are used only with the methods setData and getXXXData (XXX stands for a data type) of the function unit class FedmIscFunctionUnit. The access constant says nothing about the data type of a parameter. This is determined only by the data type of the access method. This means in the example above you could read the bus address shown either as an integer or a string or another plausible data type.

OBID® and OBID i-scan® are registered trademarks

Field Detail

FEDM_ISC_FU_TMP_MUX_ADR

static final java.lang.String FEDM_ISC_FU_TMP_MUX_ADR
Access constant for multiplexer address in communication protocols.
This constant addresses one byte in Data Container TMPDATA_MEM for temporary protocol data.
For more information about the constant, please refer to the system manual.

The access constant can be used with the Function Units:

HF Multiplexer

HF DynamicAntenna Tuner

UHF Multiplexer
